org.cef.callback

Interface CefCommandLine


  • public interface CefCommandLine
    Class used to create and/or parse command line arguments. Arguments with '--', '-' and, on Windows, '/' prefixes are considered switches. Switches will always precede any arguments without switch prefixes. Switches can optionally have a value specified using the '=' delimiter (e.g. "-switch=value"). An argument of "--" will terminate switch parsing with all subsequent tokens, regardless of prefix, being interpreted as non-switch arguments. Switch names are considered case-insensitive.(用于创建和分析命令行参数的类。带有'--'，'-'和'/'(在Windows上)前缀的参数被认为是开关。开关将始终位于任何不带开关前缀的参数之前。开关可以选择使用'='分隔符指定一个值（例如“-switch=value”）。参数“--”将终止开关解析，所有后续令牌（无论前缀如何）都将被解释为非开关参数。开关名称不区分大小写。)
